long currentTime = System.nanoTime();  used to count current time in screen. 1.000.000.000 nanoseconds = 1 second
System.out.println("Current Time: " + currentTime);
long currentTime2 = System.currentTimeMillis() is usable too but less precise

the entity class stores variables that will be used in player, monster and NPC classes

things need to be public when you want to access from other packages.

bufferedimage describes an image with an accessible buffer of image data